  "texts": [
    "Each PDF (panels left to right) is a compact 2×2 diagnostic combining: (top-left) finite-size scaling of the Liouvillian rapidity gap κ vs chain length L for several t N values; (top-right) ordered real parts of rapidities (highlighting modes near zero); (bottom-left) nearest-neighbour spacing distribution P (s) for the rapidities' real parts with Poisson (dashed) and Wigner-Dyson GOE (dot-dash) references; and (bottom-right) site-resolved weight of the slowest-decaying mode.",
    "The three panels show, from left to right: (a) uniform dissipation on all sites; (b) a single localized dissipator; and (c) two localized dissipators.",
    "At λ = 0.5 the uniform case displays the largest gaps and spacing statistics closer to Wigner-Dyson (indicative of strong mode mixing), while sparse localized dissipators show smaller gaps and more extended-to-intermediate localization signatures."
  ],
